{
  "stem": "3804.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I didn't have what to do, so I did it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, one day, after about one day or two, I didn't think he spoke.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And later, suddenly, I had him asking me, are you the man who captured-- captured me?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, how do you know?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know, because I remember still the words uno momentito, senor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and that gave me the opening to ask him questions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Holocaust, you know, is a very difficult thing, as I said before.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You can use the Holocaust-- it's a [? rule ?] for many, many stories.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's not-- I don't justify the name, Holocaust, because there have been many brave stories, children's stories, women.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the world, as I said before, is frightening and the-- if you don't come to the read the stories.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anne Frank, you'll hear, is not a Holocaust story.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's a Holocaust-- it is a story for a young woman in a situation that gives you some very brave and very wonderful story.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] so what I want to say is that, to talk to him, is only because he questioned me and all this.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, what I want to say is-- something else is-- [COUGHS] when you-- you say millions of people, I said I've never seen 6 million people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I don't-- can't understand it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't think anybody can see 6 million laying on-- on-- on one place, and you can see it, describe it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Nobody can describe it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Many times, 6 million, and all this kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I said, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "What I want to do is I want to ask him very simple questions that bother me the most, is about the son.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
